casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Jay, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Jay, 130 Ohio St.3d 239, 2011-Ohio-5161.]

(No. 2009-1915 Submitted September 21, 2011 Decided October 12, 2011.) William D. Mason, Cuyahoga County Prosecuting Attorney, and T. Allan Regas and Lisa Williamson, Assistant Prosecuting Attorneys, for appellee. Jeffrey Jay, pro se.

{¶ 1} The cause is remanded to the court of appeals for application of State v. Dunlap, 129 Ohio St.3d 461, 2011-Ohio-4111, 953 N.E.2d 816.

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, Cupp, and McGee Brown, JJ., concur.
